Purchased.code <- as.character(social_Ads$Purchased)
Purchased.code[Purchased.code=="1"]="No"
Purchased.code[Purchased.code=="0"]="Yes"
social_Ads <- data.frame(social_Ads,Purchased.code)
#graphic and visualization

Ads_Gender<-ggplot(social_Ads,aes(x=Gender)) + 
  geom_bar(aes(fill=Purchased.code),position = "fill")+
  theme_classic()+
  labs(title="Gender VS Purchased in Ads social networking",x="Gender",y="Rate")
Ads_Gender

Ads_Eduction <-ggplot(social_Ads,aes(x=Eduction)) + geom_bar(aes(fill=Purchased.code),position = "fill")+
  theme_classic()+
  labs(title="Eduction VS Purchased in Ads social networking",x="Eduction",y="Rate")
Ads_Eduction

Ads_MaritalStatus <-ggplot(social_Ads,aes(x=MaritalStatus)) + geom_bar(aes(fill=Purchased.code),position = "fill")+
  theme_classic()+
  labs(title="Marital Status VS Purchased in Ads social networking",x="Marital Status",y="Rate")
Ads_MaritalStatus

Ads_EstimatedSalary <-ggplot(social_Ads,aes(x=EstimatedSalary)) + 
  geom_density(aes(fill=Purchased.code),alpha=0.7)+
  theme_classic()+labs(title="Salary and Purchased on social networking",x="EstimateSalary",y="Rate")
Ads_EstimatedSalary

Ads_Age <-ggplot(social_Ads,aes(x=Age)) + 
  geom_density(aes(fill=Purchased.code),alpha=0.7)+
  theme_classic()+labs(title="Age and Purchased on social networking",x="Age",y="")
Ads_Age

Ads_occu <-ggplot(social_Ads,aes(x=occupation)) +

#Purchased.code
#decision tree
new_social_Ads <- social_Ads[,c(-1,-2,-6)]
dim(new_social_Ads)
## [1] 400   7
tree_model_socail_Ads <- tree(Purchased.code~.,new_social_Ads)
plot(tree_model_socail_Ads)
text(tree_model_socail_Ads,pretty = 0)

tree_pred_social <- predict(tree_model_socail_Ads,new_social_Ads,type="class")
table(tree_pred_social,Purchased.code)

## tree_pred_social  No Yes
##              No  126  15

#Cross Validation 
set.seed=(3)
train = sample(1:nrow(new_social_Ads),200)
new_social_Ads.train = new_social_Ads[train,]
new_social_Ads.test  = new_social_Ads[-train,]

Purchased.train = Purchased.code[train]
Purchased.test = Purchased.code[-train]
#build the tree model for train data
tree_model_socail_Ads_train <- tree(Purchased.code~.,new_social_Ads.train)
plot(tree_model_socail_Ads_train)
text(tree_model_socail_Ads_train,pretty = 0)

#predict the outcome for the test data use the tree model
tree_pred1_social_Ads_test <- predict(tree_model_socail_Ads_train,new_social_Ads.test,type="class")
table(tree_pred1_social_Ads_test)
## tree_pred1_social_Ads_test
##  No Yes 
##  66 134
set.seed(3)
cv.social_Ads = cv.tree(tree_model_socail_Ads_train,FUN=prune.misclass)
names(cv.social_Ads)
## [1] "size"   "dev"    "k"      "method"
plot(cv.social_Ads$size,cv.social_Ads$dev,type="b")

#pruning the tree
prune.social.Ads <- prune.misclass(tree_model_socail_Ads_train,best=3)
plot(prune.social.Ads)
text(prune.social.Ads,pretty=0)

tree_pred2_social_Ads <- predict(prune.social.Ads,new_social_Ads.test,type="class")
table(tree_pred2_social_Ads,Purchased.test)
##                      Purchased.test
## tree_pred2_social_Ads  No Yes

glm_new_social_Ads <- glm(Purchased.code~Age+EstimatedSalary+Eduction,
                          data=new_social_Ads, family = binomial)
